metadata.name: Celestial Objects #18
metadata.description:
Celestial Objects is a generative collection imagining planets and stars in the space, with light and shadows being key themes. 

The artwork is primarily rendered using hundreds of thousands of points (more than a million in some cases) to create different aspects of the output including the sky textures, shooting stars and shadows on the planets. 

Celestial Objects is coded in p5.js, and please note that it takes 5-15 seconds for each output to render.

Controls (in live view): 
Press [2] to render 2000x2000px image
Press [4] to render 4000x4000px image
Press [s] to save the current view (default window size or 2000px or 4000px image)

metadata.name: Eyeshadow Roses #823
metadata.description:
"Eyeshadow Roses" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

Painterly roses randomly overprinted with heavy streaks of ink. 

The roses grow by a sequence of three spirals, every new spiral smaller and superimposed on the former.  After the roses are fully formed, a random mask of heavy ink is algorithmically screened over the flowers in a pattern of horizontal or vertical lines, occasionally fully flooding the painting. The accumulation of choices evokes graffiti or printmaking. The sequence of choices are interpreted by the computer according to the algorithm. The beauty of these choices are determined by the viewer.

Each piece takes roughly 10 seconds to generate.

Artist: @sarah_ridgley
Press [s] to save the image
JavaScript / p5js | script size: 11kb

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #312
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden ‚Äútemplate‚Äù canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‚Äòtemplate‚Äô image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: FleurDesSquare #51
metadata.description:
'FleurDesSquare' is a generative art series blending fibonacci and squares.
Sometimes calm, sometimes chaotic. 
Hints at floral patterns emerge.  

22 colour palettes
8% chance of cracked border
34% chance of colour overlay 
21% chance of inverted colours also leading to white background

50% secondary royalties to the minter  

Thanks to all collectors and shoutouts to Circolors for the support <3 
Made with p5js

metadata.name: MOBO // HASH #32
metadata.description:
A generative exploration of the MOBO kind.

My goal here was simple... to create a series of pieces that I would genuinely want to collect myself. Style, color, the odd pop culture reference, and a nod to some of my earlier pieces/characters. I sincerely hope you enjoy this collection.

These characters are made up of more than 100 PNG layers. The under-the-hood wizardry is courtesy of the PureSpider FXHASH PFP Token Generator.

2k x 2k resolution.
